node.text:
Reminded of seeing the beaches of the Central American coast glide by from space.  Barra de La Cruz in Oaxaca, Mexico, one of the finest.

#swellfromspace

node.text:
Days when you get to work with your heroes.

Suited up by three-time Shuttle astronaut and my own personal hero Stephanie Wilson as she trains for future missions.

This last spacewalk training had part of what astronauts will do outside the real @iss in a couple weeks!

node.text:
What’s more beautiful than a tropical island in the South Pacific from space?

It’s incredible people.

So wonderful to meet students of #Samoa and share the things that are possible through hard work, passion, and tech!

Big thanks to the US Embassy in Samoa for the opportunity.

#swellfromspace

node.text:
Just as stunning from 9000 feet as from 250 miles. 

The Front Range west of #Denver and #Boulder is one of the most distinctive lines on Earth. Had to give those mountains a test run after seeing them from above. Being immersed in the landscapes we saw from the @ISS — my new favorite way to explore.

node.text:
Never gets old.

50 years ago today, one of only a handful of human mission rockets launched to the moon for Apollo 15. 

The next rocket to make the journey is stacked and getting ready as part of NASA’s Space Launch System for the @nasaartemis mission.

We’re going.

Learning trail running to explore wild places and loving the challenge of a new sport to train with friends!

node.text:
Back to your other happy place! 

Great to train with you in your first time back in the T-38 jet simulator since you got back from space, @astrovicglover! Had to sport my Crew-1 pride in your honor. Look forward to real training flights soon too…hopefully with fewer jet malfunctions!

node.text:
What’s the view from the back seat of the T-38? 

Check it out in the reflection in my visor.

Great training flights this week in the NASA jet that we use to hone our skills reacting to fast problems with crew coordination!
